      { question: "How often should you clean baseboards?", answer: "A full deep cleaning every two to three months is the right frequency for most homes. Quick standing passes with a microfiber wrapped scrub brush every two to three weeks remove fresh dust before it accumulates and extends the time between deep cleanings. Homes with pets, young children, or open floor plans where dust tracks freely across multiple rooms benefit from the more frequent maintenance. Applying a dryer sheet at the end of each cleaning extends the visible cleanliness of the trim significantly." }
